    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Chrysophyllum ferrugineum are its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, which are primarily attributed to its content of flavonoids and saponins. The plant's extracts have been shown to exhibit antimicrobial properties, effectively inhibiting the growth of various pathogens, including bacteria and fungi, thereby preventing infections and promoting wound healing. Additionally, Chrysophyllum ferrugineum has been found to possess analgesic and antipyretic properties, providing relief from pain and fever, respectively. The plant's bioactive compounds, including volatile oils and phenolic acids, also contribute to its hepatoprotective effects, safeguarding the liver from damage and promoting its regeneration. Furthermore, Chrysophyllum ferrugineum has been reported to possess anticancer properties, inhibiting the proliferation of cancer cells and inducing apoptosis, thereby slowing down tumor growth and progression.",
