    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Chrysophyllum ferrugineum are infusion, tincture, decoction, tea, and salve. Chrysophyllum ferrugineum infusion is prepared by steeping the leaves in boiling water to treat fever, rheumatism, and diarrhea. The tincture is obtained by soaking the leaves in a solvent like ethanol to create a concentrated extract used for similar purposes. Decoction is made by boiling the roots in water to treat liver and kidney problems, and tea is prepared by infusing the leaves in hot water to alleviate fever and cough. The salve is a topical preparation made by mixing the leaves with a carrier oil and is used for treating skin conditions such as eczema and wounds.",
