    "taxonomy": "Chrysophyllum ferrugineum is classified as a species of plant in the family Sapotaceae, which is a family of flowering plants commonly known as sapotes or soapberries. This family consists of around 100 species of trees and shrubs, most of which are native to tropical and subtropical regions. Chrysophyllum ferrugineum is native to tropical Africa, where it grows in a variety of habitats, including forests and grasslands. The plant is a medium-sized tree with a broad, spreading canopy and a straight, columnar trunk. Its classification is further divided into the kingdom Plantae, the clade Angiosperms, the clade Eudicots, and the clade Asterids.",
